 bolt in the same way.";i:14;s:56:"As you tighten the bolts the chain will tighten as well.";i:15;s:89:"Make sure that the chain does not get over stretched because it may snap if that happens.";i:16;s:79:"The trolley rides on the T-rail and is attached to both ends of the door chain.";i:17;s:132:"Once you identify the trolley note that the chain is attached to a stationary bracket at the end of the trolley closest to the door.";i:18;s:80:"The other end of the chain is attached to a bolt that is restrained by two nuts.";i:19;s:48:"These nuts are what controls the tension of the.";i:20;s:83:"Chain Bolt This is a 12 Chain adjusting bolt to attach the chain to a sliding gate.";i:21;s:76:"Have order from Gatehouse before parts are always right and prices are good.";i:22;s:85:"Bought 2 new 12 bolts to replace rusted out ones and these were PERFECT replacements.";i:23;s:60:"Once the power is out give the emergency release rope a tug.";i:24;s:63:"This should remove the opener connections from the garage door.";i:25;s:67:"You can then use your step ladder to look at the carriage assembly.";i:26;s:132:"The adjustment bolt a bolt with threads which the chain is connected to has a pair of adjusting nuts on either side of the assembly.";i:27;s:122:"To tighten the drive chain start by closing your garage door turning off the power and pulling the emergency release rope.";i:28;s:83:"These steps are all done for the sake of safety and should be considered necessary.";i:29;s:75:"Once done using your user manual for the opener locate the adjustment bolt.";i:30;s:74:"Stop Bolt To remove the trolley from the stop bolt follow the steps below.";i:31;s:322:"First visually verify that the trolley is against the stop boltMake sure the garage doorway is clear of persons or obstructionsRelease the door from the garage door opener by pulling the Emergency Release HandleManually bring the door to the closed positionLoosen the chain or belt by adjusting the outer nut 4 to 5 turns.";i:32;s:137:"